Gather all mutations per sample

mode <- sapply(CD2Mutant, function(z) {
  mut <- unlist(strsplit(z,split='[:]'))
  if (mut[2] %in% unique(data$Mutagen)) {
    if (mut[1] == 'N2') return('Mutagen') else return('Interaction')
  }
  else return('MA')
})

df <- data.frame(number = c((log10(rowSums(Y)[mode == 'MA'])),
                            (log10(rowSums(Y)[mode == 'Mutagen'])),
                            (log10(rowSums(Y)[mode == 'Interaction']))),
                 x = c(1:sum(mode == 'MA'),1:sum(mode == 'Mutagen'),1:sum(mode == 'Interaction')),
                 name = CD2Mutant[names(c((log10(rowSums(Y)[mode == 'MA'])),
                            (log10(rowSums(Y)[mode == 'Mutagen'])),
                            (log10(rowSums(Y)[mode == 'Interaction']))))],
                 real_name = names(c((log10(rowSums(Y)[mode == 'MA'])),
                            (log10(rowSums(Y)[mode == 'Mutagen'])),
                            (log10(rowSums(Y)[mode == 'Interaction'])))),
                 mode = c(rep('MA',sum(mode == 'MA')),
                          rep('Mutagen', sum(mode == 'Mutagen')),
                          rep('Interaction', sum(mode == 'Interaction'))))

df_median <- data.frame(y = c(sapply(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'MA']), function(x) log10(mean(rowSums(Y[CD2Mutant == x,])))),
                              sapply(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'Mutagen']), function(x) log10(mean(rowSums(Y[CD2Mutant == x,])))),
                              sapply(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'Interaction']), function(x) log10(mean(rowSums(Y[CD2Mutant == x,]))))),
                        name = c(unique(as.character(df$name[df$mode == 'MA'])),
                                 unique(as.character(df$name[df$mode == 'Mutagen'])),
                                 unique(as.character(df$name[df$mode == 'Interaction']))),
                        mode = c(rep('MA',length(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'MA']))),
                                 rep('Mutagen',length(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'Mutagen']))),
                                 rep('Interaction',length(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'Interaction'])))),
                        stringsAsFactors = F)
df$number <- c((log10(rowSums(Y[,1:96])[mode == 'MA'])),
               (log10(rowSums(Y[,1:96])[mode == 'Mutagen'])),
               (log10(rowSums(Y[,1:96])[mode == 'Interaction'])))

df_median <- data.frame(y = c(sapply(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'MA']), function(x) mean(log10(rowSums(Y[CD2Mutant == x,1:96])))),
                              sapply(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'Mutagen']), function(x) mean(log10(rowSums(Y[CD2Mutant == x,1:96])))),
                              sapply(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'Interaction']), function(x) mean(log10(rowSums(Y[CD2Mutant == x,1:96]))))),
                        name = c(unique(as.character(df$name[df$mode == 'MA'])),
                                 unique(as.character(df$name[df$mode == 'Mutagen'])),
                                 unique(as.character(df$name[df$mode == 'Interaction']))),
                        mode = c(rep('MA',length(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'MA']))),
                                 rep('Mutagen',length(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'Mutagen']))),
                                 rep('Interaction',length(unique(df$name[df$mode == 'Interaction'])))),
                        stringsAsFactors = F)
df_median <- df_median[order(df_median$y,decreasing = F),]

df_median_global <- data.frame(y = log10(c(median(10**df_median$y[df_median$mode == 'MA']),
                                           median(10**df_median$y[df_median$mode == 'Mutagen']),
                                           median(10**df_median$y[df_median$mode == 'Interaction']))), mode = c('MA','Mutagen','Interaction'))

Estimate mutation rates

counts <- rowSums(Y[,99:119])[names(CD2Mutant)[grep('N2:Rad',CD2Mutant)]]
doses <- data$Drug.concentration[match(names(CD2Mutant)[grep('N2:Rad',CD2Mutant)],data$Sample)]
rad.data <- data.frame(y = counts, x = doses / 80) # adjust to watever dose you like
model <- glm(y ~ x, family = stats::poisson(link = 'identity'), data = rad.data)
coef(summary(model))
